        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Forms containing a Zend_Form_Element_Hash are not supported by Zend_Test_PHPUnit. The form will not pass as long as you do not send the token as well generated by Zend_Form_Element_Hash. \r\nSee discussion at [http:\/\/www.nabble.com\/Zend_Test_PHPUnit-and-hashed-form-elements-td18796568.html]\r\n\r\nA solution might be to retrieve the name of the hash element as well as the hash from Zend_Session and add it by default as $_POST variables:\r\n\r\n{code}$this->request->setPost(array($form->element->getName() => $this->session->getToken()));{code}\r\n*This example is not working.* It's just a thought. I'll see whether I can find a working solution."
        },
