                    },
                    "body": "Matthew, what do you think is the best way to handle it?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stas",
                        "name": "stas",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Malyshev",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-25T10:02:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-25T10:02:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40506",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dget",
                        "name": "dget",
                        "displayName": "Daniel Getelman",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry for poor formatting, first time commenting. I was able to solve this by creating a new Zend_Form_Element_Hash object in the test. \r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\n$csrf = new Zend_Form_Element_Hash(\"csrf\");\r\n      $this->request->setMethod('POST')->setPost(\r\n                                 array(\r\n...\r\n                                       'csrf' => $csrf->getHash(),\r\n                                       ));\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dget",
                        "name": "dget",
                        "displayName": "Daniel Getelman",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-17T09:04:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-17T09:04:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40507",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dget",
                        "name": "dget",
                        "displayName": "Daniel Getelman",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As it turns out, the above didn't actually solve it. I just had another error that masked it.\r\n\r\nFor reference, the discussion link doesn't work, but http:\/\/zend-framework-community.634137.n4.nabble.com\/Zend-Test-PHPUnit-and-hashed-form-elements-td652290.html does.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dget",
                        "name": "dget",
                        "displayName": "Daniel Getelman",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-17T09:30:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-17T09:30:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43962",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{code}\r\n$csrf = new Zend_Form_Element_Hash(\"csrf\");\r\n\r\n$hash = $csrf->getHash();\r\n$csrf->initCsrfToken();\r\n$csrf->initCsrfValidator();\r\n\r\n$this->request->setMethod('POST')->setPost(\r\narray(\r\n...\r\n'csrf' => $hash,\r\n));\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThat would work",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-07T05:30:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-07T05:30:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48738",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is more of a documentation\/awareness issue than an issue with {{Zend_Form_Element_Hash}} itself. I suggest updating the manual entry for that component to outline how forms which use it can be unit tested.  Example:\r\n{code}\r\nIndex: documentation\/manual\/en\/module_specs\/Zend_Form-StandardElements.xml\r\n===================================================================\r\n--- documentation\/manual\/en\/module_specs\/Zend_Form-StandardElements.xml\t(revision 24514)\r\n+++ documentation\/manual\/en\/module_specs\/Zend_Form-StandardElements.xml\t(working copy)\r\n@@ -522,6 +522,37 @@\r\n             The 'formHidden' view helper is used to render the element in the\r\n             form.\r\n         <\/para>\r\n+\r\n+        <note>\r\n+            <title>Testing forms containing Zend_Form_Element_Hash<\/title>\r\n+            <para>\r\n+                When unit testing a form containing a <classname>Zend_Form_Element_Hash<\/classname> \r\n+                it is necessary to call <methodname>initCsrfToken<\/methodname> and \r\n+                <methodname>initCsrfValidator<\/methodname> before attempting to\r\n+                validate the form.  The hash value of the <classname>Zend_Form_Element_Hash<\/classname> \r\n+                element must also be injected into the array of values passed as the\r\n+                argument to <methodname>Zend_Form::isValid<\/methodname>\r\n+            <\/para>\r\n+            <example id=\"zend.form.standardElements.hash.unittesting\">\r\n+                <title>Simple example of testing a CSRF-protected form<\/title>\r\n+                <programlisting language=\"php\"><![CDATA[\r\n+public function testCsrfProtectedForm() \r\n+{\r\n+    $form = new Zend_Form();\r\n+    $form->addElement(new Zend_Form_Element_Hash('csrf'));\r\n+\r\n+    $csrf = $form->getElement('csrf');\r\n+    $csrf->initCsrfToken();\r\n+    $csrf->initCsrfValidator();\r\n+\r\n+    $this->assertTrue($form->isValid(array(\r\n+        'csrf' => $csrf->getHash()\r\n+    )));\r\n+}]]><\/programlisting>\r\n+\r\n+            <\/example>\r\n+        <\/note>\r\n+        \r\n     <\/sect2>\r\n \r\n     <sect2 id=\"zend.form.standardElements.Image\">\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThoughts?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
